{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0b7bab75-924a-4cdd-baba-8ff080ceb4a9","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax\n\nThe VSTest `--filter` syntax (`FullyQualifiedName~X&Category=Y`) is replaced by the MTP `--filter` syntax. The equivalent is:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Trait['Category']='Smoke'\"\n```\n\nKey differences:\n- `&` → `and` (logical operator)\n- `Category=Smoke` → `Trait['Category']='Smoke'` (traits are accessed via `Trait['key']='value'`)\n- `~` (contains) still works for substring matching\n\n### 2. Missing test runner package\n\nYour `.csproj` enables MTP (`UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner`) but is missing the required runner package. Add it:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n```\n\nWithout it, `dotnet test` won't discover or filter tests under MTP.\n\n### Quick reference\n\n| VSTest filter | MTP filter |\n|---|---|\n| `Category=Smoke` | `Trait['Category']='Smoke'` |\n| `&` | `and` |\n| `\\|` | `or` |\n| `FullyQualifiedName~Foo` | `FullyQualifiedName~Foo` |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"575b7d9c-606f-4aa4-bbfb-35807ae8db59","outputTokens":340},"id":"9ba14e34-4c42-40a4-b0e6-4fd97b4b4216","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:06:47.615Z","parentId":"6974c952-c106-40f9-ae91-ee09dab03542"}
